{{耶稣}}
'''耶稣的历史性'''主要关注文献来源在何种程度上表明[[耶稣|拿撒勒人耶稣]]是作为一个历史人物而存在的。它不仅根据时间和地点的背景去研究“历史中发生的真实事件”，而且同样研究现代的观察者如何知道“历史中发生的真实事件”的。<ref>[//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/William_J._Hamblin William J. Hamblin], professor of history at Brigham Young University. </ref>第二个问题是紧密地与分析第一手资料的可靠性以及其它历史证据的历史研究实践、方法联系在一起的。它还关注耶稣是否是一个[[拿细耳人|拿细耳人]]问题。<ref>Numbers 1:6-21</ref><ref>E. Meyers & J. Strange, Archaeology, the Rabbis, & Early Christianity Nashville: Abingdon, 1981; Article “Nazareth” in the Anchor Bible Dictionary. </ref>

幾乎所有當代研究古代史的學者都同意《聖經》裡描述的耶穌是史實人物，耶穌基督是西元三十年左右生活於今日巴勒斯坦一帶的歴史人物、接受施洗者約翰受洗並且被釘死在十字架上，及耶穌基督是《聖經》里提及的那個人物且對人類文明造成深遠影響等這幾點，迨無爭議，這些內容已經成為[[科學共識|學界共識]]，研究古代歷史的學者，不論是否是基督徒，都同意這些內容。在2011年一篇回顧現代學術界狀況的文章中，[[巴特·葉爾曼|巴特·葉爾曼]]寫道：「耶穌當然是史實人物，幾乎所有夠格的古代史學者，不論是否是基督徒，都會同意這點的。」<ref>{{cite book|first=Bart|last=Ehrman|year=2011|title=Forged: writing in the name of God – Why the Bible's Authors Are Not Who We Think They Are|isbn=978-0-06-207863-6 |url=https://books.google.com/?id=MtOMO8i4GLoC |publisher=HarperCollins |page=285}}</ref>[[Richard_A._Burridge|Richard A. Burridge]]（一名[[英格蘭教會|英格蘭教會]]的牧師與聖經學者）則說道：「有些人主張耶穌基督是教會虛構的人物、耶穌未曾存在過，對此，我必須說，我沒聽過有任何值得敬重且持批判觀點的學者依舊有這樣的主張。」<ref>{{cite book|title=Jesus Now and Then|url=https://archive.org/details/jesusnowthen0000burr|first1= Richard A.|last1= Burridge |first2= Graham |last2= Gould|year=2004| isbn= 978-0-8028-0977-3 |page=[https://archive.org/details/jesusnowthen0000burr/page/34 34] |publisher=Wm. B. Eerdmans Publishing}}</ref>

使用历史调查的标准衡量方法，幾乎所有的[[新約聖經|新约]]学者和近东历史学家都認為，耶穌毫無疑義地是史實人物<ref name="Blomberg">{{cite book|title=The Historical Reliability of the Gospels|last=Blomberg|first=Craig L.|publisher=InterVarsity Press|year=2007|isbn=9780830828074}}</ref><ref name="Carrier">{{cite book|title=On the Historicity of Jesus: Why we might Have Reason for Doubt|url=https://archive.org/details/onhistoricityofj0000carr|last=Carrier|first=Richard Lane|publisher=Sheffield Phoenix Press|year=2014|isbn=9781909697355}}</ref><ref name="fox">{{cite book|title=The Classical World: An Epic History from Homer to Hadrian|last=Fox|first=Robin Lane|publisher=Basic Books|year=2005|isbn=978-0465024971|page=48}}</ref><ref name="nobbs">{{cite web|url=http://www.abc.net.au/religion/articles/2012/12/24/3660194.htm|title=Best of 2012: The irreligious assault on the historicity of Jesus|accessdate=17 June 2014|last1=Dickson|first1=John|website=Abc.net.au|archive-date=2018-05-13|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180513080506/http://www.abc.net.au/religion/articles/2012/12/24/3660194.htm|dead-url=no}}</ref>，虽然他们对耶稣的信仰、教导以及福音书中描述的耶稣生命细节的准确性有不同的看法。<ref name="MAPowell168">{{cite book|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=IJP4DRCVaUMC|title=Jesus as a Figure in History: How Modern Historians View the Man from Galilee|publisher=Westminster John Knox Press|year=1998|isbn=978-0-664-25703-3|author=Mark Allan Powell|access-date=2017-02-27|archive-date=2017-03-13|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170313202515/https://books.google.com/books?id=IJP4DRCVaUMC|dead-url=no}}</ref>{{Rp|168–173}}虽然学者批评耶稣文献的宗教偏见和合理方法的欠缺，但这些批评者几乎都普遍支持耶稣的历史性，并拒绝基督神话理论，该理论认为耶稣不曾在历史中存在过。<ref name="Powell1998">{{cite book|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=IJP4DRCVaUMC|title=Jesus as a Figure in History: How Modern Historians View the Man from Galilee|publisher=Westminster John Knox Press|year=1998|isbn=978-0-664-25703-3|pages=168|author=Mark Allan Powell|access-date=2017-02-27|archive-date=2017-03-13|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170313202515/https://books.google.com/books?id=IJP4DRCVaUMC|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name="Houlden2003">{{cite book|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=GjvmQgAACAAJ|title=Jesus in History, Thought, and Culture: Entries A - J.|publisher=ABC-CLIO|year=2003|isbn=978-1-57607-856-3|author=James L. Houlden|access-date=2017-02-27|archive-date=2021-04-14|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210414054512/https://books.google.com/books?id=GjvmQgAACAAJ|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name="VVoorst14">{{cite book|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=lwzliMSRGGkC|title=Jesus Outside the New Testament: An Introduction to the Ancient Evidence|publisher=Wm. B. Eerdmans Publishing|year=2000|isbn=978-0-8028-4368-5|pages=14|author=Robert E. Van Voorst|access-date=2017-02-27|archive-date=2020-08-19|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200819143206/https://books.google.com/books?id=lwzliMSRGGkC|dead-url=no}}</ref>

“耶稣的历史性”与“[[历史中的耶稣|历史中的耶稣]]”的相关研究不同，后者指的是对耶稣生命的学术重构，主要是建立在对福音文本的批判性分析上。<ref name="LevineJr.2006">{{cite book|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=wMbEyeDSQQgC|title=The Historical Jesus in Context|date=16 October 2006|publisher=Princeton University Press|isbn=0-691-00992-9|pages=1–2|author1=Amy-Jill Levine|author2=Dale C. Allison Jr.|author3=John Dominic Crossan}}</ref><ref name="Ehrman1999">{{cite book|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=vzszmQEACAAJ|title=Jesus: Apocalyptic Prophet of the New Millennium|publisher=Oxford University Press|year=1999|isbn=978-0-19-512473-6|pages=ix–xi|author=Bart D. Ehrman}}</ref><ref name="Dunn2003">{{cite book|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=G4qpnvoautgC|title=Jesus Remembered|publisher=Wm. B. Eerdmans Publishing|year=2003|isbn=978-0-8028-3931-2|pages=125–127|author=James D. G. Dunn|access-date=2017-02-27|archive-date=2021-04-26|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210426221922/https://books.google.com/books?id=G4qpnvoautgC|dead-url=no}}</ref>相反，历史性作为一个研究主题与历史本身不同，它涉及到两个不同的根本问题。首先，它关注社会变革的系统过程；其次，它关注社会背景和文献来源的作者意图，通过这些元素，我们可以建立历史事件的真相，从而将神话记录与事实情况分离开来。<ref>Hare Rom and Moghadda Fathali "Historicity, Social Psychology and Change" in Rochmore, Tom and Margolis, Tom (2008) "History, Historicity and Science" (Ashgate)</ref>

== 文献来源 ==
[[File:First_century_Iudaea_province.gif|缩略图]]]]

关于耶稣的生活和教导的主要记载是他死后几年由第三方叙述的。基督教的圣经代表了成为基督教[[教会法|经典]]的文献来源，而且，在第一世纪存在许多与耶稣相关的伪经。<ref>{{Cite book|title=The Historical Jesus|last=Theissen|first=Gerd|last2=Merz|first2=Annette|publisher=Fortress Press|year=1996|isbn=978-0-8006-3122-2|location=Minneapolis MN|pages=17–62}}</ref>这些来源的真实性和可靠性已被许多学者质疑，并且福音书中提到的事件很少被普遍接受。<ref name="MAPowell168" />{{Rp|181}} 

非基督文献来源也用于研究和建立耶稣的历史性，其中包括犹太来源，如[[弗拉維奧·約瑟夫斯|弗拉维奥·约瑟夫斯]]，以及罗马来源，如[[塔西佗|塔西佗]]。这些来源通常与基督教的来源（如[[cmn:保罗书信|保罗书信]]和[[cmn:对观福音|对观福音]]）相提并论，它们通常是相互独立的（例如犹太来源并不引用罗马来源），并且它们之间的相似性和差异性被用于鉴证过程。<ref name="Camber121">''The Cambridge Companion to Jesus'' by Markus N. A. Bockmuehl 2001 [//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Special:BookSources/0521796784 ISBN 0521796784] pp. 121–125</ref><ref name="ChiltonEvans1998">{{cite book|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=AJM9grxOjjMC|title=Studying the Historical Jesus: Evaluations of the State of Current Research|publisher=BRILL|year=1998|isbn=90-04-11142-5|pages=460–470|author1=Bruce David Chilton|author2=Craig Alan Evans|access-date=2017-02-27|archive-date=2020-10-04|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201004084608/https://books.google.com/books?id=AJM9grxOjjMC|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name="Blomberg431">''Jesus and the Gospels: An Introduction and Survey'' by Craig L. Blomberg 2009 [//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Special:BookSources/0805444823 ISBN 0-8054-4482-3] pp. 431–436</ref><ref>[//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Historicity_of_Jesus#refVanVoorst2000 Van Voorst (2000)] pp. 39–53</ref>

[[弗拉維奧·約瑟夫斯|弗拉维奥·约瑟夫斯]]的《犹太古史》写于公元93-94年左右，它在第[[wikisource:The_Antiquities_of_the_Jews/Book_XVIII#Chapter_3|18]]和[[wikisource:The_Antiquities_of_the_Jews/Book_XX#Chapter_9|20]]篇中提到圣经的耶稣。一般学者的看法是，虽然那个较长的、称为Testimonium Flavianum段落总的来说很可能不是真实的，但人们普遍认为，它最初是由一个真正的核心构成，然后才遭到基督教的篡改或伪造。<ref>{{cite book|title=Jewish Traditions in Early Christian Literature|last=Schreckenberg|first=Heinz|year=1992|isbn=90-232-2653-4|author2=Kurt Schubert}}</ref><ref>{{cite book|title=The Cradle, the Cross, and the Crown:  An Introduction to the New Testament|last=Kostenberger|first=Andreas J.|year=2009|isbn=0-8054-4365-7|author2=L. Scott Kellum|author3=Charles L. Quarles}}</ref>在[[弗拉維奧·約瑟夫斯|约瑟夫斯]]另一处提到耶稣的地方，研究约瑟夫斯的学者认为，“很少有人质疑[[弗拉維奧·約瑟夫斯|约瑟夫斯]]”在《犹太古代史》的[[wikisource:The_Antiquities_of_the_Jews/Book_XX#Chapter_9|20篇9.1处]]中提到耶稣的地方的“真实性”，而且只有少数学者有争议。<ref name="JospehusM662">''The new complete works of Josephus'' by Flavius Josephus, William Whiston, Paul L. Maier [//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Special:BookSources/0825429242 ISBN 0-8254-2924-2] pp. 662–663</ref><ref>''Josephus XX'' by [//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Louis_H._Feldman Louis H. Feldman] 1965, [//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Special:BookSources/0674995023 ISBN 0674995023] p. 496</ref>在第20篇第9章中，总共有三处提到“耶稣”的名字：“耶稣，称为基督”（即“弥赛亚”）；“耶稣，[犹太大祭司]达姆内斯（Damneus）之子”，（两者都在第1段中）；和“耶稣[另一位犹太大祭司]迦玛列（Gamaliel）之子”（在第4段中）。

罗马历史学家[[塔西佗|塔西佗]]在他的[[編年史_(塔西佗)|编年史]]，大约写于公元116年）的[[wikisource:The_Annals_(Tacitus)/Book_15#44|15篇44章]]提到一个名为 “Christus”的人以及他被[[cmn:本丟·彼拉多|彼拉多]]处决的事件。<ref>P.E. Easterling, E. J. Kenney (general editors), ''The Cambridge History of Latin Literature'', p. 892 (Cambridge University Press, 1982, reprinted 1996). </ref>[[塔西佗|塔西佗]]对基督徒持有消极的评价，因此这段文字极不可能被一个基督徒抄写者伪造的。<ref name="VVoorst39">Robert E. Van Voorst, ''Jesus Outside the New Testament: An Introduction to the Ancient Evidence'', Wm. B. Eerdmans, 2000. p 39- 53</ref> [[塔西佗|塔西佗]]对耶稣的提及现在被广泛地接受作为对基督被钉十字架的独立的确认，<ref name="EddyB127">Eddy, Paul; Boyd, Gregory (2007). </ref>虽然一些学者以各种不同的理由质疑这段文字的真实性。<ref>F.F. Bruce,''Jesus and Christian Origins Outside the New Testament'', (Grand Rapids: Eerdmans, 1974) p. 23</ref><ref>{{Cite book|url=https://books.google.com/?id=3ZU97DQMH6UC&pg=PA83|title=The historical Jesus: a comprehensive guide|publisher=Fortress Press|year=1998|isbn=978-0-8006-3122-2|location=Minneapolis|page=83|author1=Theissen, Gerd|author2=Merz, Annette}}</ref><ref name="martin">{{cite book|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=wWkC4dTmK0AC&pg=PA52&dq=historicity+of+jesus&hl=en&sa=X&ei=o-_8U5-yEtTH7AbBpoCoAg&ved=0CCUQ6AEwAg#v=onepage&q=tacitus&f=false|title=The Case Against Christianity|last=Martin|first=Michael|pages=50–51|access-date=2017-02-27|archive-date=2019-06-08|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190608184554/https://books.google.com/books?id=wWkC4dTmK0AC&pg=PA52&dq=historicity+of+jesus&hl=en&sa=X&ei=o-_8U5-yEtTH7AbBpoCoAg&ved=0CCUQ6AEwAg#v=onepage&q=tacitus&f=false|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{Cite book|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=1CZbuFBdAMUC&pg=PA45&dq=historicity+of+jesus&hl=en&sa=X&ei=o-_8U5-yEtTH7AbBpoCoAg&ved=0CEoQ6AEwCQ#v=onepage&q=tacitus&f=false|title=The Historical Jesus in the Twentieth Century: 1900-1950|last=Weaver|first=Walter P.|date=1999-07-01|publisher=A&C Black|year=|isbn=9781563382802|location=|pages=|language=en|chapter=|access-date=2017-02-27|archive-date=2020-10-02|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201002200922/https://books.google.com/books?id=1CZbuFBdAMUC&pg=PA45&dq=historicity+of+jesus&hl=en&sa=X&ei=o-_8U5-yEtTH7AbBpoCoAg&ved=0CEoQ6AEwCQ#v=onepage&q=tacitus&f=false|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{Cite book|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=jCaopp3R5B0C&pg=PA100&dq=interpolations+in+tacitus&hl=en&sa=X&ei=CRf-U9-VGZCe7AbxrIDQCA&ved=0CCAQ6AEwATge#v=onepage&q=interpolations%20in%20tacitus&f=false|title=Secret of Regeneration|last=Hotema|first=Hilton|date=1998|publisher=Health Research Books|year=|isbn=9780787304294|location=|pages=|language=en|chapter=|access-date=2017-02-27|archive-date=2020-10-02|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201002184216/https://books.google.com/books?id=jCaopp3R5B0C&pg=PA100&dq=interpolations+in+tacitus&hl=en&sa=X&ei=CRf-U9-VGZCe7AbxrIDQCA&ved=0CCAQ6AEwATge#v=onepage&q=interpolations%20in%20tacitus&f=false|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>''Jesus'', University Books, New York, 1956, p.13</ref><ref>{{Cite book|title=Evidence for Jesus (Jesus Library)|url=https://archive.org/details/evidenceforjesus0000fran|last=France|first=RT|authorlink=RT France|publisher=Trafalgar Square Publishing|year=1986|isbn=0-340-38172-8|pages=[https://archive.org/details/evidenceforjesus0000fran/page/19 19]–20}}</ref>

历史学家{{link-en|Michael Grant|Michael_Grant_(author)}}写道：如果我们将一个用于判断其它包含着历史材料的古代作品的标准应用于新约，那么，我们不能再拒绝耶稣的存在，也不能拒绝大量异教徒人物的存在，这些人物作为历史人物从来没有被质疑过。

== 福音书的历史可靠性 ==
[[File:Byzantinischer_Maler_um_1020_003.jpg|缩略图]]

[[福音书|福音书]]的历史可靠性是指四个新约福音作为历史文献的可靠性和历史特征。一些学者认为[[四福音|四福音]]的作者是假托的、未知的<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.huffingtonpost.com/bart-d-ehrman/the-bible-telling-lies-to_b_840301.html|title=Who wrote the Bible and Why it Matters|date=|last=Ehrman|first=Bart|website=HuffingtonPost.com|access-date=21 November 2016|archive-date=2018-02-08|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180208190104/https://www.huffingtonpost.com/bart-d-ehrman/the-bible-telling-lies-to_b_840301.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>，在這四个成为经典的福音书中，並没有甚麼历史可靠性。<ref>Craig Evans, "Life-of-Jesus Research and the Eclipse of Mythology," Theological Studies 54 (1993) p. 5</ref><ref name="Charles H. Talbert pg 42">Charles H. Talbert, What Is a Gospel? </ref><ref name="Jesus 1995">“The Historical Figure of Jesus," Sanders, E.P., Penguin Books: London, 1995, p. 3.</ref><ref name="ReferenceC">Fire of Mercy, Heart of the Word (Vol. </ref><ref name="religion-online.org">{{Cite web|url=http://www.religion-online.org/showchapter.asp?title=1116&C=1230|title=A Historical Introduction to the New Testament (Harper and Row, 1963)|last=Grant|first=Robert M.|website=Religion-Online.org|access-date=|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100621102923/http://religion-online.org/showchapter.asp?title=1116&C=1230|archivedate=2010-06-21}}</ref>

大多数古代学者都同意耶稣存在，<ref name="Ehrman285">In a 2011 review of the state of modern scholarship, [//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bart_Ehrman Bart Ehrman] (a secular agnostic) wrote: "He certainly existed, as virtually every competent scholar of antiquity, Christian or non-Christian, agrees" B. Ehrman, 2011 ''Forged : writing in the name of God'' [//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Special:BookSources/9780062078636 ISBN 978-0-06-207863-6]. p. 285</ref><ref>[//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Robert_M._Price Robert M. Price] (an atheist) who denies the existence of Jesus agrees that this perspective runs against the views of the majority of scholars: Robert M. Price "Jesus at the Vanishing Point" in ''The Historical Jesus: Five Views'' edited by James K. Beilby & Paul Rhodes Eddy, 2009 InterVarsity, [//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Special:BookSources/0830838686 ISBN 0830838686] p. 61</ref><ref name="Grantmajority">[//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Michael_Grant_(author) Michael Grant] (a [//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Classicist classicist]) states that "In recent years, 'no serious scholar has ventured to postulate the non historicity of Jesus' or at any rate very few, and they have not succeeded in disposing of the much stronger, indeed very abundant, evidence to the contrary." in ''Jesus'' by Michael Grant 2004 [//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Special:BookSources/1898799881 ISBN 1898799881] p. 200</ref><ref name="Burridge34">''Jesus Now and Then'' by Richard A. Burridge and Graham Gould (April 1, 2004) [//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Special:BookSources/0802809774 ISBN 0802809774] p. 34</ref>但是学者关于圣经在耶稣叙述时描述的特定事件的历史性有不同看法。<ref name="MAPowell168" />{{Rp|181}}只有两个“几乎是普遍同意”的事件，这就是：耶稣接受[[施洗約翰|施洗约翰]]的洗礼，并在一年或三年后，他被罗马总督本丢·彼拉多钉十字架。在历史真实性上有争议的元素包括：[[耶稣诞生|耶稣诞生]]的两个记载，[[耶稣的神迹|神迹]]事件（[[耶稣的神迹|将水变成酒，行走在水面上和复活]]），以及关于被钉十字架的某些细节。<ref>James G. D. Dunn, ''Jesus Remembered'', (Eerdmans, 2003) pp. 779–781.</ref><ref>[//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bruce_M._Metzger Bruce M. Metzger]'s ''Textual Commentary on the Greek New Testament'': {{Bibleref2|Luke|24:51}} is missing in some important early witnesses, {{Bibleref2|Acts|1}} varies between the [//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Alexandrian_text-type Alexandrian] and [//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Western_text-type Western versions].</ref>

对观福音书是有关耶稣的历史信息以及他创立的宗教运动的主要信息来源。<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.britannica.com/biography/Jesus|title=Jesus Christ|work=Encyclopædia Britannica. 2010. Encyclopædia Britannica Online|quote=The Synoptic Gospels, then, are the primary sources for knowledge of the historical Jesus|access-date=27 November  2010|archive-date=2020-05-10|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200510143612/https://www.britannica.com/biography/Jesus|dead-url=no}}</ref>这些用希腊语写成的宗教福音书——[[馬太福音|马太福音]]，[[馬可福音|马可福音]]，[[路加福音|路加福音]]——叙述了一个名为耶稣、说[[亞拉姆語|阿拉姆语]]的犹太人的生命、事工、被钉十字架和[[cmn:耶稣复活|复活]]的事件。关于文本的起源有不同的假设，因为[[新约|新约]]的福音书是用希腊语写成并用于希腊社会的，<ref>Mark Allan Powell (editor), ''The New Testament Today'', p. 50 (Westminster John Knox Press, 1999). </ref>后来译成叙利亚语，拉丁语和科普特语，<ref>Stanley E. Porter (editor), ''Handbook to Exegesis of the New Testament'', p. 68 (Leiden, 1997). </ref>尽管有人说马太福音的一个版本可能是用亚拉姆语写成的。<ref>Lenski, Richard CH (2008) [1943], "The Hypothesis of an Original Hebrew", The Interpretation of St. Matthew's Gospel 1–14, pp. 12–14</ref>

第四个福音，即[[约翰福音|约翰福音]]，与前三个福音书有很大的不同。历史学家在研究福音书的可靠性时通常研究[[使徒行传|使徒行传]]的历史可靠性，因为使徒行传似乎是与路加福音出于同一作者。<ref>{{cite book|title=Dictionary of Jesus and the Gospels|date=2013|publisher=IVP Academic|isbn=978-0830824564|edition=2nd|page=541|last1=Green|first1=Joel B.}}</ref>

历史学家通过将真实的、可靠的信息与可能的发明、夸张和变更等部分区分开来，从而对福音书进行了批判性的分析。<ref name="Sanders">Sanders, E. P. ''The historical figure of Jesus''. </ref>由于新约中的文本变体（20-40万）比它的使徒书信的变体（约14万）还多，<ref>[//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bart_D._Ehrman Bart D. Ehrman]: ''[//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Misquoting_Jesus Misquoting Jesus – The Story Behind Who Changed the Bible and Why]'', p. 90 [http://www.biblicalstudies.org.uk/pdf/jma/nts-mss_5_arlandson.pdf (review)] {{Wayback|url=http://www.biblicalstudies.org.uk/pdf/jma/nts-mss_5_arlandson.pdf |date=20150923185208 }}.</ref>因此学者使用文本批评的方法来确定哪些福音变体在理论上可被视为“本源的”。为了回答这个问题，学者必须质疑这些问题：谁写了福音书，当他们写福音书时，他们写作的目的是什么，<ref name="Rhodes-Eddy08">Paul Rhodes Eddy & Gregory A. Boyd, ''The Jesus Legend:A Case for the Historical Reliability of the Synoptic Jesus Tradition.'' (2008, Baker Academic).309-262.</ref>作者使用了什么文献来源，这些来源有多可靠，这些来源在时间上距离他们叙述的故事有多远，这些来源后来是否发生了改变。学者还可以考察文档的内部证据，看看文档是否错误地引用了希伯来Tanakh的文本，是否出现了不正确的地理信息，是否作者在隐藏信息，或者，是否作者在虚构某个预言。<ref name="nazorene">The [//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Gospel_of_Matthew Gospel of Matthew] claims, the [//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Nazarene_(title) title Nazarene] for Jesus was derived from the prophecy "He will be called a Nazorean" ({{bibleref2|Matthew|2:22–23|NRSV}}), despite the lack of any [//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Old_Testament Old Testament] source.</ref>最后，学者转向外部文献来源，包括早期教会领袖、教会以外的作家（主要是犹太作家和希腊-罗马史学家）的证词，他们更可能会批评教会；学者同时也需考虑考古证据。

== 通常被接受为历史的事件 ==

学者们对福音书叙事中提到的耶稣生平的细节以及他的教导的意义持有广泛不同的意见，只有两个“几乎普遍同意”的事件，这就是：耶稣接受[[聖若翰洗者|施洗者约翰]]的洗礼，并在一年或三年后，被罗马总督[[本丟·彼拉多|本丟·彼拉多]][[十字架|钉十字架]]。<ref name="Hertzog1">''Prophet and Teacher: An Introduction to the Historical Jesus'' by William R. Herzog (4 Jul 2005) [//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Special:BookSources/0664225284 ISBN 0664225284] pp. 1–6</ref><ref name="JDunn339">''Jesus Remembered'' by James D. G. Dunn 2003 [//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Special:BookSources/0802839312 ISBN 0-8028-3931-2] p. 339 states of baptism and crucifixion that these "two facts in the life of Jesus command almost universal assent".</ref><ref name="autogenerated145">{{cite book|title=Jesus: A Revolutionary Biography|url=https://archive.org/details/jesusrevolutiona00cros|publisher=HarperOne|year=1995|isbn=0-06-061662-8|page=[https://archive.org/details/jesusrevolutiona00cros/page/145 145]|quote=That he was crucified is as sure as anything historical can ever be, since both Josephus and Tacitus ... agree with the Christian accounts on at least that basic fact.|author=Crossan, John Dominic}}</ref>
[[File:Sapsaphas_Madaba.jpg|缩略图]]
[[File:Bronzino-Christ-Nice.jpg|缩略图]]
根据新约学者[[詹姆斯·鄧恩|詹姆斯·邓恩]]，几乎所有现代学者都认为[[耶稣受洗|耶稣受洗]]和被[[耶穌被釘十字架|钉十字架]]在历史上是确定的。他说“耶稣生平的这两个事实几乎是得到普遍确认的”，并且“几乎是无可置疑的，这两个事件是试图澄清什么是耶稣的使命，为什么这是耶稣的使命等问题的明显出发点”。John P. Meier将耶稣钉十字架视为历史事实，并指出，基于尴尬标准，基督徒不会虚构他们的领袖痛苦地死亡的事件。<ref>John P. Meier "How do we decide what comes from Jesus" in''The Historical Jesus in Recent Research''by James D. G. Dunn and Scot McKnight 2006 ISBN 1-57506-100-7 pp. 126–128</ref>尴尬标准同样也用来支持施洗约翰施洗耶稣的历史性，因为这个事件是[[早期基督教|早期基督教会]]从来不想虚构的故事。<ref name="Whois31">''Who Is Jesus?'' by John Dominic Crossan, Richard G. Watts 1999 [//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Special:BookSources/0664258425 ISBN 0664258425] pp. 31–32</ref><ref name="Casey35">''Jesus of Nazareth: An Independent Historian's Account of His Life and Teaching'' by Maurice Casey 2010 [//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Special:BookSources/0567645177 ISBN 0-567-64517-7] p. 35</ref>基于这个标准，同时考虑到约翰是为了罪的减轻而受洗，并且考虑到耶稣被视为没有罪的，因此发明这个故事是毫无目的，而且还可能带来一个尴尬——因为，这个故事把约翰置于耶稣之上。<ref name="Powell47">''Jesus as a figure in history: how modern historians view the man from Galilee'' by Mark Allan Powell 1998 [//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Special:BookSources/0664257038 ISBN 0-664-25703-8] p. 47</ref><ref>''The historical Jesus: a comprehensive guide'' by Gerd Theissen, Annette Merz 1998 [//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Special:BookSources/0800631226 ISBN 0-8006-3122-6] p. 207</ref>

Amy-Jill Levine总结了这种情况，指出人们“对于耶稣生活的基本轮廓存在一种共识”，因为大多数学者都同意耶稣是由施洗约翰施洗的，在一到三年的时间里与犹太当局辩论关于上帝的话题，聚集追随者，并被罗马总督彼拉特（在位时间公元26-36年）钉十字架。<ref name="AmyJill4">{{Cite book|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=wMbEyeDSQQgC|title=The Historical Jesus in Context|last=Amy-Jill Levine|last2=Dale C. Allison Jr.|last3=John Dominic Crossan|date=16 October 2006|publisher=Princeton University Press|isbn=0-691-00992-9|pages=4}}</ref>关于他之前的生活、童年、家庭和居住地点则有很多争议。对于这些问题，正典[[四福音|四福音]]几乎完全沉默。<ref>Eisenmann, Robert, (2001), "James the Brother of Jesus: The Key to Unlocking the Secrets of Early Christianity and the Dead Sea Scrolls"</ref><ref>Butz, Jeffrey (2005), "The Brother of Jesus and the Lost Traditions of Christianity" (Inner Traditions)</ref><ref>Tabor, James (2012), "Paul and Jesus: How the Apostle Transformed Christianity" (Simon & Schuster)</ref>

学者将对其他情节的肯定性有不同程度的看法。有些人认为关于耶稣和他的追随者有八个元素可以被视为历史事实，即：<ref name="Evans37">''Authenticating the Activities of Jesus'' by Bruce Chilton and Craig A. Evans 2002 [//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Special:BookSources/0391041649 ISBN 0391041649] pp. 3–7</ref>
* 耶稣受了施洗约翰的洗礼。 
* 他召唤门徒。 
* 他在圣殿带来争议。 
* 耶稣在耶路撒冷附近被罗马人钉死。
* 耶稣是加利利人。 
* 他的活动只限于[[加利利|加利利]]和[[犹地亚|犹地亚]]。 
* 耶稣死后，他的门徒继续传教。 
* 他的一些门徒受到迫害。
学术界并不普遍同意这个扩展清单。<ref name="MAPowell117">''Jesus as a Figure in History: How Modern Historians View the Man from Galilee'' by Mark Allan Powell (1 Nov 1998) [//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Special:BookSources/0664257038 ISBN 0664257038] p. 117</ref>

[[米書拿|米書拿]]（约公元200年）可能提到了耶稣，并反思了早期犹太传统将耶稣描绘为巫师或魔术师。<ref name="Leslie693">In ''Jesus: The Complete Guide'' edited by J. L. Houlden (8 Feb 2006) [//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Special:BookSources/082648011X ISBN 082648011X] pp. 693–694</ref><ref name="PeterS141">''Jesus in the Talmud'' by Peter Schäfer (24 Aug 2009) [//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Special:BookSources/0691143188 ISBN 0691143188] pp. 141 and 9</ref><ref name="Blom280">''Jesus and the Gospels: An Introduction and Survey'' by Craig L. Blomberg (1 Aug 2009) [//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Special:BookSources/0805444823 ISBN 0805444823] p. 280</ref>其他提到耶稣和他被处决的地方是[[塔木德|塔木德]]，其目的是抹黑他的行为，但不否认他的存在。<ref name="Bammel393">''Jesus and the Politics of his Day'' by E. Bammel and C. F. D. Moule (30 Aug 1985) [//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Special:BookSources/0521313449 ISBN 0521313449] p. 393</ref><ref name="Kellum107">Kostenberger, Andreas J.; Kellum, L. Scott; Quarles, Charles L. (2009). </ref>

自18世纪以来，对[[对历史中耶稣的探索|历史中的耶稣进行了三次学术探索]]，每次都有不同的特点，并且基于不同的研究标准，这些研究标准往往是在那个阶段中发展起来的。<ref name="BenQ9">''The Jesus Quest: The Third Search for the Jew of Nazareth by Ben Witherington (May 8, 1997) [//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Special:BookSources/0830815449 ISBN 0830815449] pp. 9–13''</ref><ref name="AlanP19">''Jesus as a Figure in History: How Modern Historians View the Man from Galilee'' by Mark Allan Powell (1 Jan 1999) [//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Special:BookSources/0664257038 ISBN 0664257038] pp. 19–23</ref>在这些过程中构建的耶稣形象往往彼此不同，而且也不同于福音书中描述的教条性的形象。
[[File:CompositeJesus.JPG|左]]
目前，对历史中的耶稣的现代学术研究关注的是历史上耶稣的可能性。<ref>''John, Jesus, and History'' Volume 1 by Paul N. Anderson, Felix Just and Tom Thatcher (14 Nov 2007) [//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Special:BookSources/1589832930 ISBN 1589832930] p. 131</ref><ref>[//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/John_P._Meier John P. Meier] "Criteria: How do we decide what comes from Jesus?" in ''The Historical Jesus in Recent Research'' by James D. G. Dunn and Scot McKnight (15 Jul 2006) [//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Special:BookSources/1575061007 ISBN 1575061007] p. 124 "Since in the quest for the historical Jesus almost anything is possible, the function of the criteria is to pass from the merely possible to the really probable, to inspect various probabilities, and to decide which candidate is most probable. </ref>

在第三次探索中，主流的耶稣形象可以根据主题而分为几类：启示的先知，有领导魄力的治疗师，愤世嫉俗的哲学家，犹太的弥赛亚和社会变革的先知，<ref name="Cradel124">''The Cradle, the Cross, and the Crown: An Introduction to the New Testament'' by Andreas J. Köstenberger, L. Scott Kellum 2009 [//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Special:BookSources/9780805443653 ISBN 978-0-8054-4365-3] pp. 124–125</ref><ref name="CambHist23">''The Cambridge History of Christianity'', Volume 1 by Margaret M. Mitchell and Frances M. Young (Feb 20, 2006) [//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Special:BookSources/0521812399 ISBN 0521812399] p. 23</ref>但是，每个形象上都存在学术上的分歧，对于构建这些形象的学术方法也存在着分歧。<ref name="Porter74">''Images of Christ'' (Academic Paperback) by Stanley E. Porter, Michael A. Hayes and David Tombs (Dec 19, 2004) [//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Special:BookSources/0567044602 ISBN 0567044602] [//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/T&T_Clark T&T Clark] p. 74</ref><ref>''The Jesus Quest: The Third Search for the Jew of Nazareth'' by Ben Witherington (May 8, 1997) [//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Special:BookSources/0830815449 ISBN 0830815449] p. 197</ref>然而，在形象之间有重叠的属性，学者不认同某些属性时可能对其他属性有所认同。<ref name="familiar20">''Familiar Stranger: An Introduction to Jesus of Nazareth'' by Michael James McClymond (Mar 22, 2004) [//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Special:BookSources/0802826806 ISBN 0802826806] pp. 16–22</ref>
[[File:Bautismo_de_Cristo_por_Navarrete_el_Mudo.jpg|缩略图]]
虽然对耶稣的存在抱有广泛的学术共识，对他的生命大致轮廓也存在着基本共识，但在每次探索中对耶稣形象的构建经常彼此不同，和福音书中描绘的形象也不一样。 在肖像之间有重叠的属性，虽然有时候两个学者可能同意一些属性，但他们可能会不同意其他属性，没有一个历史中的耶稣形象能满足广大的学者群体。<ref>[//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Amy-Jill_Levine Amy-Jill Levine] in the ''The Historical Jesus in Context'' edited by Amy-Jill Levine et al. 2006 Princeton University Press [//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Special:BookSources/9780691009926 ISBN 978-0-691-00992-6] p. 1: "no single picture of Jesus has convinced all, or even most scholars"</ref>

一个大多数人赞同的观点是，几乎所有在现代研究古代的学者都同意耶稣是史實的人物，大多数[[聖經研究|圣经学者]]和古典历史学家认为，「耶稣未曾存在」的理论，已經有效地被驳倒了。<ref name="DunnPaul35">[//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/James_D._G._Dunn James D. G. Dunn] (1974) ''Paul's understanding of the death of Jesus'' in ''Reconciliation and Hope. ''</ref>今天没有证据表明，在古代反对基督教的人曾否认耶稣的存在。<ref name="Rahner730">''Encyclopedia of theology: a concise Sacramentum mundi'' by Karl Rahner 2004 [//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Special:BookSources/0860120066 ISBN 0-86012-006-6] pp. 730–731: "The few non-Christian sources [e.g. </ref><ref name="voorst15">Van Voorst, Robert E (2000). </ref>{{link-en|Geoffrey Blainey|Geoffrey_Blainey}}指出，“少数学者认为耶稣……甚至不存在”，他们“正确地指出，和耶稣同时代的著作对他的提及是极其罕见的。”<ref>Geoffrey Blainey; ''[//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/A_Short_History_of_Christianity A Short History of Christianity]''; Viking; 2011; pp. xix–xx</ref> Bart Ehrman承认，“耶稣没有被任何和他同时代的罗马文献来源所提及”，但他却坚持，其他来源的确支持耶稣的存在，<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.huffingtonpost.com/bart-d-ehrman/did-jesus-exist_b_1349544.html|title=Did Jesus Exist?|date=March 20, 2012|last=Ehrman|first=Bart D.|publisher=[[The_Huffington_Post|The Huffington Post]]|accessdate=2017-02-27|archive-date=2018-08-22|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180822020811/https://www.huffingtonpost.com/bart-d-ehrman/did-jesus-exist_b_1349544.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>而 Richard Carrier 和Raphael Lataster则断言，没有新约之外耶稣存在的独立证据。<ref>{{Cite book|title=Jesus Did Not Exist: A Debate Among Atheists|last=Lataster|first=Raphael|authorlink=Raphael Lataster|date=November 12, 2015|isbn=1514814420|page=418|chapter=Afterword by Richard Carrier|quote=[T]here is no independent evidence of Jesus’s existence outside the New Testament. All external evidence for his existence, even if it were fully authentic (though much of it isn’t), cannot be shown to be independent of the Gospels, or Christian informants relying on the Gospels. None of it can be shown to independently corroborate the Gospels as to the historicity of Jesus. Not one single item of evidence. Regardless of why no independent evidence survives (it does not matter the reason), no such evidence survives.}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://theconversation.com/weighing-up-the-evidence-for-the-historical-jesus-35319|title=Weighing up the evidence for the ‘Historical Jesus’|date=December 14, 2014|last=Lataster|first=Raphael|publisher=[[The_Conversation_(website)|The Conversation (website)]]|quote=There are no existing eyewitness or contemporary accounts of Jesus. All we have are later descriptions of Jesus’ life events by non-eyewitnesses, most of whom are obviously biased.|access-date=2017-02-27|archive-date=2021-02-23|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210223061935/https://theconversation.com/weighing-up-the-evidence-for-the-historical-jesus-35319|dead-url=no}}</ref> 

某些学者，特别是欧洲学者，最近声称，虽然耶稣的存在有很多可能性，但是很难确认这个耶稣是圣经中的耶稣，人们应该在这个问题上作更多学术研究和讨论。<ref name="ThompsonVerenna2013">{{Cite book|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=pP9DlwEACAAJ|title='Is This Not the Carpenter?': The Question of the Historicity of the Figure of Jesus|last=Thomas L. Thompson|last2=Thomas S. Verenna|publisher=Acumen Publishing, Limited|year=2013|isbn=978-1-84465-729-2}}</ref>

== 基督神话理论 ==
[[File:Noel_Coypel_The_Resurrection_of_Christ.jpg|缩略图]]

基督神话理论认为耶稣从未存在，并且认为，如果他确实存在，那么他与基督教的建立以及福音书中的记载几乎没有任何关系。<ref>{{Cite book|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=4PkTAAAAQAAJ&pg=PA151|title=The Christian mythology unveiled, lectures|last=Mitchell|first=Logan|publisher=Cousins|year=1842|page=151|quote=Jesus Christ in the New Testament, has no reference whatever to any event that ever did in reality take place upon this globe; or to any personages that ever in truth existed: and that the whole is an astronomical allegory, or parable, having invariably a primary and sacred allusion to the sun, and his passage through the signs of the zodiac; or a verbal representation of the phenomena of the solar year and seasons. (Image of [https://books.google.com/books?id=4PkTAAAAQAAJ&pg=PR3&img=1&zoom=3&hl=en&sig=ACfU3U2AIPMkTeyiajzAlC6kQckFI73S-Q Title page] & [https://books.google.com/books?id=4PkTAAAAQAAJ&pg=PA151&img=1&zoom=3&hl=en&sig=ACfU3U2D2OB_X2_DjhZ2f18Id3iUR0TVuA&ci=75%2C140%2C815%2C1057&edge=0 p. 151] at Google Books)|access-date=2017-02-27|archive-date=2019-12-17|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191217044311/https://books.google.com/books?id=4PkTAAAAQAAJ&pg=PA151|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>[//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bart_Ehrman Bart Ehrman], ''Did Jesus Exist?'' </ref><ref name="OTHOJ">{{Cite book|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=UJX5oAEACAAJ|title=On the Historicity of Jesus: Why We Might Have Reason for Doubt|last=Carrier|first=Richard|authorlink=Richard Carrier|publisher=Sheffield Phoenix Press Limited|year=2014|isbn=978-1-909697-49-2|page=52|quote=[T]he basic thesis of every competent mythologist, then and now, has always been that Jesus was originally a god just like any other god (properly speaking, a demigod in pagan terms; an archangel in Jewish terms; in either sense, a deity), who was later historicized.|access-date=2017-02-27|archive-date=2017-03-13|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170313211519/https://books.google.com/books?id=UJX5oAEACAAJ|dead-url=no}}</ref>

現階段这个理论在当今学者中几乎没有得到什么支持<ref>[//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Did_Jesus_Exist%3F_(Ehrman) Did Jesus exist?], [//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bart_Ehrman Bart Ehrman], 2012, Chapter 1</ref>，是基本上已經被淘汰的學說；然而，历史上，这种神话主义观点在学术界<ref>{{Cite book|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=X4t-BAAAQBAJ&pg=PT133|title=Out of My Life and Thought: An Autobiography|last=Schweitzer|first=Albert|authorlink=Albert Schweitzer|date=7 October 2014|publisher=Henry Holt and Company|isbn=978-1-4668-8294-2|page=133|quote=In the autumn of 1912, when l was already busy shopping and packing for Lambaréné, I undertook to integrate into ''The Quest of the Historical Jesus'' material from the new books that had in the meantime appeared on the subject and to rewrite sections that no longer satisfied me. I especially wanted to explain late Jewish eschatology more thoroughly and to discuss the works of John M. Robertson, William Benjamin Smith, James George Frazer, Arthur Drews, and others, who contested the historical existence of Jesus.}}</ref><ref>{{Cite book|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=Xd8AAAAAMAAJ|title=Christianity and the nature of history|last=Wood|first=Herbert George|publisher=University Press.|year=1934|page=40|quote=[T]he sociological fashion reflected in the rise of Formgeschichte lends colour to Christ-myth theories and indeed to all theories which regard Jesus as an historical but insignificant figure.}}</ref><ref>{{Cite book|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=VMhQa_43d3sC&pg=PA112|title=Independence and Exegesis: The Study of Early Christianity in the Work of Alfred Loisy (1857-1940), Charles Guignebert (1857 [i.e. 1867]-1939), and Maurice Goguel (1880-1955)|last=Jones|first=Alan H.|publisher=Mohr Siebeck|year=1983|isbn=978-3-16-144451-7|page=112|quote=In 1937, [[Paul-Louis_Couchoud|Couchoud]] published ''Jésus: Le Dieu Fait Homme'', [[Alfred_Loisy|Loisy]] replied with one of the last volumes of his vast output: ''Histoire et mythe à propos de Jésus-Christ'' (1938)}}</ref><ref>{{Cite book|url=http://cdn.theologicalstudies.net/2/2.2/2.2.5.pdf|title=Theological Studies: A brief survey of Loisy's life and work|last=A. C. COTTER, S.J.|publisher=America Press|chapter=ALFRED LOISY (1857-1940)|quote=[Loisy] came out with a vigorous attack on Couchoud's mythical theory in ''Histoire et mythe à propos de Jésus-Christ'' (1938). To Loisy's credit be it said that, to the end of his days, he maintained Jesus' historical existence against all mythmakers.|access-date=2017-02-27|archive-date=2016-10-18|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161018153656/http://cdn.theologicalstudies.net/2/2.2/2.2.5.pdf|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{Cite book|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=2XHysoHc2ksC&pg=PR16|title=Shattering the Christ Myth|last=Holding|first=James Patrick|date=June 2008|publisher=Xulon Press|isbn=978-1-60647-271-2|page=16|quote=On [[George_Albert_Wells|George Albert Wells]]: "For his first book ''The Jesus of the Early Christians'' (1971), Wells took advantage of his fluency in German to read the radical work of Drews, Bauer and others. He had access to all the books that had never been translated into English. The result was a restatement of the early-twentieth century argument that used pagan parallels and interpolation as its main planks. The book was released by a trade publisher and received critical reviews in some academic journals. None of his later works received the same sort of attention."}}</ref>中有不同程度的影响力，有些甚至成为主流学术研究的一部分，例如[[大卫·施特劳斯|大卫·施特劳斯]]的观点。<ref>{{Cite book|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=O33P7xrFnLQC&pg=PA15|title=The Historical Jesus: Five Views|last=Beilby|first=James K.|last2=Eddy|first2=Paul Rhodes|date=4 January 2010|publisher=InterVarsity Press|isbn=978-0-8308-7853-6|page=15|quote=One of the most influential figures of the “old” quest is [[David_Strauss|David Friedrich Strauss]] ([[大卫·施特劳斯|大卫·施特劳斯]]). His book ''The Life of Jesus Critically Examined'', originally published in 1835, became one of the most controversial studies of Jesus ever written.}}</ref>在一个短暂的时期内，这个理论在苏联很受欢迎，Sergey Kovalev, Alexander Kazhdan, Abram Ranovich, Nikolai Rumyantsev, Robert Wippe和 {{Internal link helper/en|Yuri Frantsev|Yuri Frantsev}}都支持这个观点。<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://pstgu.ru/download/1430825026.5_andreev_73-88.pdf|title=Дискуссия об историчности Иисуса Христа в советском религиоведении|accessdate=12 June 2015|author=А. В. Андреев|date=2015|work=Вестник ПСТГУ|publisher=|language=ru|archive-date=2015-06-13|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150613051540/http://pstgu.ru/download/1430825026.5_andreev_73-88.pdf|dead-url=no}}</ref> 然而，后来，包括Kazhdan在内的几位学者收回了对神话耶稣的看法，到80年代末，在苏联学术界中几乎不存在对这一理论的支持。<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.gumer.info/bogoslov_Buks/bogoslov/Golol/03.php|title=Богословие и национальный вопрос|accessdate=12 June 2015|author=Гололоб Г.|date=|publisher=Библиотека Гумер|language=ru|archive-date=2016-03-04|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160304114836/http://www.gumer.info/bogoslov_Buks/bogoslov/Golol/03.php|dead-url=no}}</ref>

最近，{{link-en|Richard Carrier|Richard_Carrier}}在他的《耶稣的历史性：为什么我们可能有理由去怀疑》（''On the Historicity of Jesus: Why We Might Have Reason for Doubt）''一书中指出，没有足够的“[[贝叶斯概率|贝叶斯概率]]”，也就是证据，能相信耶稣的存在。此外，他认为，耶稣的形象可能最初只是通过私人的启示和隐藏在圣经中的信息而来的，然后被雕刻成一个历史人物，以寓言的方式传达福音书中的观点。然后，这些寓言在公元一世纪基督教教会的控制权争斗中开始被认为是事实。Philip R. Davies认为，认识到耶稣历史性的不完全确定性将推动耶稣文献得到学术的尊重<ref name="bibleinterp.com">{{Cite web|url=http://www.bibleinterp.com/opeds/dav368029.shtml|title=Did Jesus Exist?|accessdate=2017-11-15|author=|date=|work=|publisher=The Bible and Interpretation|archive-date=2015-09-23|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150923184812/http://www.bibleinterp.com/opeds/dav368029.shtml|dead-url=no}}</ref>在Jesus Project中的R. Joseph Hoffmann 指出，耶稣越变得模糊、含混和不确定，就有越多的学者研究他，而不是相反。<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://richardcarrier.blogspot.com/2009/01/amherst-conference.html|title=Amherst Conference|date=January 10, 2009|last=Carrier|first=Richard|access-date=2017-02-27|archive-date=2021-01-21|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210121215424/http://richardcarrier.blogspot.com/2009/01/amherst-conference.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>

和Carrier不同，一些著名的专家已经发表同行评审的关于耶稣历史性书籍，这些书籍使用了在这个主题上最新的文献，其中包括Dale Allison, Bart Ehrman, Amy-Jill Levine 和 Geza Vermes他们都相信历史耶稣的存在，反对基督神话理论，但他们倾向于将历史耶稣看作是一个犹太传教士，他从来没有声称自己神，也没有任何意图去建立一个宗教。然而，一些学者却不同意这种共识。<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.strangenotions.com/questioning-the-historicity-of-jesus/|title=Questioning the Historicity of Jesus|accessdate=6 April 2016|last=Dr. Richard Carrier|publisher=Brandon Vogt|quote=The hypothesis that Jesus never really existed has started to gain more credibility in the expert community. Some now agree historicity agnosticism is warranted, including Arthur Droge (professor of early Christianity at UCSD), [[Kurt_Noll|Kurt Noll]] (associate professor of religion at Brandon University), and [[Thomas_L._Thompson|Thomas Thompson]] (renowned professor of theology, emeritus, at the University of Copenhagen). Others are even more certain historicity is doubtful, including [[Thomas_L._Brodie|Thomas Brodie]] (director emeritus of the Dominican Biblical Centre at the University of Limerick, Ireland), [[Robert_M._Price|Robert Price]] (who has two Ph.D.’s from Drew University, in theology and New Testament studies), and myself (I have a Ph.D. in ancient history from Columbia University and have several peer reviewed articles on the subject). Still others, like Philip Davies (professor of biblical studies, emeritus, at the University of Sheffield), disagree with the hypothesis but admit it is respectable enough to deserve consideration.|archive-date=2019-04-27|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190427070430/https://strangenotions.com/questioning-the-historicity-of-jesus/|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{Cite journal|title=IT'S OFFICIAL: WE CAN NOW DOUBT JESUS' HISTORICAL EXISTENCE|last=Lataster|first=Raphael|date=29 March 2016|journal=Think|issue=43|doi=10.1017/s1477175616000117|volume=15|pages=65–79|quote=Think, Volume 15, Issue 43, Summer 2016, Published online by Cambridge University Press}}</ref><ref>{{Cite journal|title=Ehrman and Brodie on Whether Jesus Existed: A Cautionary Tale about the State of Biblical Scholarship|url=http://ocabs.org/journal/index.php/jocabs/article/view/80/47|last=Tom Dykstra|date=2015|journal=The Journal of the Orthodox Center for the Advancement of Biblical Studies (JOCABS)|issue=1|volume=8|page=29|quote=As for the question of whether Jesus existed, the best answer is that any attempt to find a historical Jesus is a waste of time. It can’t be done, it explains nothing, and it proves nothing. [Vol. 8, No. 1 (2015)]|access-date=2017-02-27|archive-date=2021-03-22|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210322150925/http://ocabs.org/journal/index.php/jocabs/article/view/80/47|dead-url=no}}</ref>

